<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> seeing how many times has vision almost gone under for the same reason.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Exactly zero times.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> And i specifically remeber in the last 4 months or so 2 seperate aoccasions Vision was SOOO close to breaking up that members started looking for other guilds.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
There will occasionally be, in any organization, people who don't like the compensation, the atmosphere, an individual or subgroup of the organization or the goals of the organization.<br>
<br>
On the whole, we have one of the largest (not most uber, just large) memberships at over 130 members. We have open discussions on our message boards about any subject someone wants to bring up (unless it's totally inflammatory like some of the posts on NAG) and we generally work towards a loot system and goals that meet the needs of the majority of our members.<br>
<br>
If you've chosen to speak with a couple disgruntled people out of our 130+ roster, then you have gotten a skewed view of the situation.<br>
<br>
<br>
Nena's quote sums it up well.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Loot issues have a lot more to do with commitment than they do with how it's handed out.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
We take the long view of things in the guild. We do what's best for the guild overall. Maybe this month it's outfit all the warriors in ToV, and maybe next it's take out epic mobs for wizard and shaman epics.<br>
<br>
The majority of our membership take the long view and have little if any problem with how loot is distributed. It's going to benefit the guild and benefit ~them~ as a part of it. When they do have a problem, there are people in the officer ranks who deal with their concerns genuinely.<br>
<br>
As an officer and founding member, I can assure you that we've have no secret-squirrel meetings about how to oust Palimax or dissolve the guild.<br>
<br>
<br>
Many of us are father-son, mother-daughter, sister-brother and best friend combinations. We talk on the phone, meet for beers and bowling or dinner on a regular basis, and have an annual get-together in Vegas.<br>
<br>
We've maintained a nice solid base of people since the beginning and I expect we'll be around and together when Verant shuts down these servers. <p><font face=arial>Membrayne VolcanoEyes<br>Arch Mage of <a href="http://www.guildvision.org">Vision</a><br> Master of Elements</font></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/umembrayne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Membrayne</A> at: 1/14/02 9:20:20 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucrist0.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crist0</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/14/02 9:19:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=804.topic&index=112>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I don't hate you Blizz</span><hr size=1> Hehe I can tell you this much Palimax:<br>
